title: Interlocking Standard Liberator Barrel
description:
Whipped this up in about 1:30-2:00.

Print and assemble with regular Liberator parts.

The locking mechanism works by you inserting the pins into the holes and twisting counterclockwise.

I have designed this to the best of my ability, but do not hold me responsible for anything that this is used for or is the result of.

I have not actually printed these parts, but they should work.

Best of luck!
